#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.39:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Natumhākavagga"
msgstr "4. It’s Not Yours"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Anudhammasutta"
msgstr "39. In Line With the Teachings"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.41"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.39:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.39:1.2"
msgid "“Dhammānudhammappaṭipannassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ayamanudhammo hoti "
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant is practicing in line with the teachings, this "
"is what’s in line with the teachings. "

#. VAR: nibbidābahulo → nibbidābahulaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.39:1.3"
msgid ""
"yaṃ rūpe nibbidābahulo vihareyya, vedanāya nibbidābahulo vihareyya, saññāya "
"nibbidābahulo vihareyya, saṅkhāresu nibbidābahulo vihareyya, viññāṇe "
"nibbidābahulo vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"They should live full of disillusionment for form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.39:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yo rūpe nibbidābahulo viharanto, vedanāya … saññāya … saṅkhāresu "
"nibbidābahulo viharanto, viññāṇe nibbidābahulo viharanto rūpaṃ parijānāti, "
"vedanaṃ … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … viññāṇaṃ parijānāti, "
msgstr ""
"Living in this way, they completely understand form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.39:1.5"
msgid ""
"so rūpaṃ parijānaṃ, vedanaṃ … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … viññāṇaṃ parijānaṃ "
"parimuccati rūpamhā, parimuccati vedanāya, parimuccati saññāya, parimuccati "
"saṅkhārehi, parimuccati viññāṇamhā, "
msgstr ""
"Completely understanding form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness, they’re freed from these things. "

msgctxt "sn22.39:1.6"
msgid ""
"parimuccati jātiyā jarāmaraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi "
"upāyāsehi, parimuccati dukkhasmāti vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress. They’re freed from suffering, I say.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.39:1.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
